CONQUERING DEMONS OUT HERE IN ALBUQUERQUE 😤

23.14 for 7th place today, but perspective is key; only 2.5 months of normal training since my hamstring tear, 3 seasons best, and most importantly a clutch third round throw after two fouls. Goal for indoors was to refine my approach to competing and this meet was a big step forward. There’s still more work to be done but glad to be trending upwards 🙌🏼

Also super grateful to have a stellar team helping me out behind the scenes, don’t think I coulda done it without you ✊🏼 @coach_nathan_ott @brooke_andersen @saharajayy @drbeckerthrows

This is 30 👊🏼

The last couple years of my 20’s were pretty turbulent from a career perspective. There were many times I thought my best days were behind me, and many times I’ve contemplated retirement. Surviving as a professional hammer thrower is no small feat, as the years have gone on I felt the life getting drained out of me.

But here I am, prepping for year 7 as a pro, and I’m happy I’ve stuck it out. It’s been a long, arduous road, but I’m finally feeling some hope for the first time in a while. Much gratitude for the people around me who’ve stuck it out and supported me through the tough times, and thank you to everyone in my new training environment for helping me realize I still have more to give. Onwards and upwards ✊🏼
